 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 -- NC            : No Connect. This pin has no internal connection to the device.
 -- DNU           : Do Not Use. This pin MUST NOT be connected.
 -- VCCINT        : Dedicated power pin, which MUST be connected to VCC  (FIX6).
 -- VCCIO         : Dedicated power pin, which MUST be connected to specific voltage
 --                 of its bank.
 --                  Bank 2A_T:       1.2V
 --                  Bank 2A_B:       1.2V
 --                  Bank 3A_T:       1.2V
 --                  Bank 3A_B:       1.2V
 --                  Bank 5A:       3.3V
 --                  Bank 5B:  3.3V
 -- GND           : Dedicated ground pin. Dedicated GND pins MUST be connected to GND.
 --                  It can also be used to report unused dedicated pins. The connection
 --                  on the board for unused dedicated pins depends on whether this will
 --                  be used in a future design. One example is device migration. When
 --                  using device migration, refer to the device pin-tables. If it is a
 --                  GND pin in the pin table or if it will not be used in a future design
 --                  for another purpose the it MUST be connected to GND. If it is an unused
 --                  dedicated pin, then it can be connected to a valid signal on the board
 --                  (low, high, or toggling) if that signal is required for a different
 --                  revision of the design.
 -- GND+          : Unused input pin. It can also be used to report unused dual-purpose pins.
 --                  This pin should be connected to GND. It may also be connected  to a
 --                  valid signal  on the board  (low, high, or toggling)  if that signal
 --                  is required for a different revision of the design.
 -- RESERVED      : Unused I/O pin, which MUST be left unconnected.
 -- RESERVED_INPUT    : Pin is tri-stated and should be connected to the board.
 -- RESERVED_INPUT_WITHOUT_WEAK_PULLUP : Pin is tri-stated without internal weak pull-up resistor.
 -- RESERVED_INPUT_WITH_WEAK_PULLUP    : Pin is tri-stated with internal weak pull-up resistor.
 -- RESERVED_INPUT_WITH_BUS_HOLD       : Pin is tri-stated with bus-hold circuitry.
 -- RESERVED_OUTPUT_DRIVEN_HIGH        : Pin is output driven high.
 -- VREFP_ADC      : If no external reference is supplied, always connect the VREFP_ADC pin to GND.
 --                  See Pin Connection Guidelines for details.
 -- VREFN_ADC      : If no external reference is supplied, always connect the VREFN_ADC pin to GND.
 --                  See Pin Connection Guidelines for details.
 -- VSIGP          : Tie this pin to GND if you do not use the Voltage Sensor feature.
 --                  See Pin Connection Guidelines for details.
 -- VSIGN          : Tie this pin to GND if you do not use the Voltage Sensor feature.
 --                  See Pin Connection Guidelines for details.
 -- DTS_CALIB      : Pins are used for Calibration of the temperature sensor during manufacturing.
 --                  They can be left open on board when not in use.
 -- RREF_SDM       : Pin is reference resister input for the PLLs of the SDM interface. 
 --                  See Pin Connection Guidelines for details.
 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------



